{"parse":{"title":"sun","pageid":1795,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Appendix:Variations of \"sun\"}}\n{{minitoc}}\n==Translingual==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{clip|mul|en:'''Sun'''danese,su:'''Sun'''da}}.\n\n===Symbol===\n{{mul-symbol}}\n\n# {{ISO 639|2&3|su|Sundanese}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{langcat|su}}\n\n==English==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|sŭn}}, {{IPA|en|/sʌn/}}\n** {{audio|en|En-uk-sun.ogg|a=RP}}\n** {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Persent101-sun.wav|a=US}}\n* {{IPA|en|/sʊn/|a=Northern England,Ireland}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ʌn|s=1}}\n* {{homophones|en|son}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{word|en|ine|sóh₂wl̥}}\n{{etymon|en|:inh|enm:sonne|tree=1}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|soen}}, {{m|enm|son}}, {{m|enm|sone}}, {{m|enm|sonne}}, {{m|enm|sun}}, {{m|enm|sune}}, {{m|enm|sunna}}, {{m|enm|sunne}}, {{m|enm|sunnæ}}, {{m|enm|synne}}, {{m|enm|zonne}}, {{m|enm|zunne}}, from {{inh|en|ang|sunna}}, {{m|ang|sunne}}, {{m|ang|sunnu|t=sun}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*sunnā}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*sunnǭ|t=sun}}, from [[heteroclitic]] [[inanimate]] {{inh|en|ine-pro||*sh₂wen-}}, oblique of {{der|en|ine-pro|*sóh₂wl̥|t=sun}}. {{col-top|2|cog}}\nCognate with {{cog|sco|sun|t=sun}}, {{cog|yol|zin|t=sun}}, {{cog|frr|san}}, {{m|frr|Sen|t=sun}}, {{cog|stq|Sunne|t=sun}}, {{cog|fy|sinne|t=sun}}, {{cog|gsw|ŝchunna}}, {{m|gsw|ŝchunnà}}, {{m|gsw|sònnò}}, {{m|gsw|sunna}}, {{m|gsw|sunnu}}, {{m|gsw|Sunnä|t=sun}}, {{cog|bar|Sun}}, {{m|bar|suna}}, {{m|bar|sune}}, {{m|bar|Sunn}}, {{m|bar|sunne|t=sun}}, {{cog|cim|sonde}}, {{m|cim|sunn}}, {{m|cim|zunna|t=sun}}, {{cog|nl|zon}}, {{m|nl|zonne|t=sun}}, {{cog|de|Sonne|t=sun}}, {{cog|li|Ṣon}}, {{m|li|Sonn}}, {{m|li|zón|t=sun}}, {{cog|nds|Sünn}}, {{m|nds|Sünne|t=sun}}, {{cog|lb|Sonn|t=sun}}, {{cog|mhn|sunn|t=sun}}, {{cog|wym|zun}}, {{m|wym|zunn|t=sun}}, {{cog|vls|zunne|t=sun}}, {{cog|yi|זון|t=sun}}, {{cog|is|sunna|t=sun}}, {{cog|gme-cgo|sune|t=sun}}, {{cog|got|𐍃𐌿𐌽𐌽𐍉|t=the Sun}}; outside of Germanic, {{cog|kw|howl|t=sun}}, {{cog|ga|súil|t=eye; expectation, hope}}, {{cog|gv|sooill|t=eye}}, {{cog|gd|sùil|t=eye; vision; glance, look; expectation, hope}}, {{cog|cy|haul}}, {{m|cy|huan|t=sun}}, {{cog|la|sōl|t=sun}}, {{cog|el|ήλιος|t=sun}}, {{cog|sq|diell|t=sun}}, {{cog|ltg,lv|saule|t=sun}}, {{cog|lt|saulė|t=sun}}, {{cog|be|со́нца|t=sun}}, {{cog|bg|слъ́нце|t=sun}}, {{cog|cs|slunce|t=sun}}, {{cog|mk|солнце}}, {{m|mk|сонце|t=sun}}, {{cog|pl|słońce|t=sun}}, {{cog|ru|со́лнце|t=sun}}, {{cog|sh|су̑нце}}, {{m|sh|sȗnce|t=sun}}, {{cog|sk|slnce|t=sun}}, {{cog|sl|sonce|t=sun}}, {{cog|uk|со́нце|t=sun}}, {{cog|ae|𐬵𐬎𐬎𐬀𐬭𐬆|t=sun}}, {{cog|ckb|خۆر|t=sun}}, {{cog|hac|وەر|t=sun; front}}, {{cog|os|хор}}, {{m|os|хур|t=sun}}, {{cog|fa|هور|tr=hur}}, {{m|fa|خور|tr=xor / xwar|t=sun}}, {{cog|sgh|хӣр|t=sun}}, {{cog|yai|хур|t=sun}}, {{cog|txb|swāñco|t=beam, ray, sunbeam}}, {{cog|hi|सूर्य}}, {{cog|sa|स्वर्|t=sun}}. Related to {{doublet|en|sol|id1=day|Sol|Surya|Helios|notext=1}}. More at {{m|en|solar}}.\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{sense|proper noun|star which Earth revolves around}} {{alter|en|Sun||capitalized}}\n* {{alter|en|sonne|sunne||obsolete spelling}}\n* {{alter|en|☉||astronomy}}\n\n====Proper noun====\n{{en-proper noun|head=the sun}}\n[[File:Skylab Solar flare.jpg|thumbnail|The Sun, photographed by Skylab 4.]]\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q525}}The [[star]] that is [[closest]] to the [[Earth]].\n#* {{RQ:Tyndale NT|format=full|Revelation|21|23|folio=cccxlij|passage=And the cite hath no nede of the '''ſunne''' nether of the mone to lyghten hit. For the bꝛynghtnes off God dyd light hitt: and the lambe was the light off hit.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1886|translator=H.L. Br&aelig;kstad|author=w:Peter Christen Asbj&oslash;rnsen|title=Folk and Fairy Tales|page=233|passage=\"I suppose I may have leave to do that!\" Yes, she could do that, he said, but there was no road to that place; it lay east of the '''sun''' and west of the moon, and she could never find her way there.}}\n#* {{RQ:Lincoln Pratt's Patients|chapter=1|passage='Twas early June, the new grass was flourishing everywheres, the posies in the yard—peonies and such—in full bloom, '''the sun''' was shining, and the water of the bay was blue, with light green streaks where the shoal showed.}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{see translation subpage|Proper noun}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{lb|en|astronomy}} A [[star]], especially when seen as the centre of any single [[solar system]].\n#* {{quote-video game|en|developer=w:BioWare|title=w:Mass Effect 2|genre=[[science fiction|Science Fiction]]|location=Redwood City|publisher=Electronic Arts|year=2010|system=PC|scene=Haestrom Codex entry|oclc=865290061|passage=Because Haestrom's '''sun''' has overwhelmed the planet's protective magnetosphere, humans foolhardy enough to venture into {{w|Geth|geth}}-controlled Haestrom must exercise extreme caution. Minutes of radiation exposure will overload shields and hours of exposure will kill.}}\n# The light and heat which are received from the [[Sun]]; [[sunshine]] or [[sunlight]].\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Winter's Tale|I|ii|passage=Lambs that did frisk in the '''sun'''.}}\n#* {{RQ:Bulwer-Lytton Rienzi|volume=I|chapter=The Knight of Provençe, and His Proposal|page=184|passage=His fair hair waved long and freely over a white and unwrinkled forehead: the life of a camp and the '''suns''' of Italy had but little embrowned his clear and healthful complexion, which retained much of the bloom of youth.}}\n# {{lb|en|figurative}} Something like the sun in brightness or splendor.\n#* {{RQ:Geneva Bible|Psalms|84|11|253|column=2|text=For the Lord God is the '''ſunne''' & ſhield ''vnto vs'': {{...}}}}\n#* {{RQ:Eikon Basilike|chapter=Upon their seizing the Kings Magazines, Forts, Navy, and Militia|page=65|passage={{...}} I will never conſent to put out the '''Sun''' of Sovereigntie to all Poſterity, {{...}}}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|chiefly|literary}} [[sunrise|Sunrise]] or [[sunset]].\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Cymbeline|act=III|scene=ii|page=381|columns=1–2|passage=''Imo''[''gen''].{{...}}Prythee ſpeake, / How many ſtore of Miles may we well rid / Twixt houre, and houre? / ''Piſ''[''anio'']. One ſcore 'twixt '''Sun''', and '''Sun''', / Madam's enough for you: and too much too. / ''Imo''[''gen'']. Why, one that rode to's Excution Man, / Could neuer go ſo ſlow: {{...}}}}\n#* {{RQ:Burton Melancholy|edition=5th|chapter=Discontents, Cares, Miseries, &c. causes|partition=1|section=2|member=3|subsection=10|page=110|passage=[W]hileſt many an hunger-ſtarved poore creature pines in the ſtreet, wants clothes to cover him, labours hard all day long, runs, rides for a trifle, fights peradventure from '''Sun''' to '''Sun''', ſick and ill, weary, full of paine and griefe, is in great diſtreſſe and ſorrow of heart.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=w:A Week on the Concord and Merrimack Rivers|page=357|author=w:Henry David Thoreau|year=1849|passage=I love these sons of earth every mother's son of them, with their great hearty hearts rushing tumultuously in herds from spectacle to spectacle, as if fearful lest there should not be time between '''sun''' and '''sun''' to see them all, and the sun does not wait more than in haying-time.|year_published=1873}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1962|title=Public Papers of the Presidents of the United States: Harry S. Truman|author=w:Harry S. Truman|page=651|passage=You see, the President has five jobs, any one of which would be more than a full-time job for one man; but I have to do all five of them between '''sun''' and '''sun'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Howling Stones|page=149|author=Alan Dean Foster|year=1997|passage=“Tomorrow at first '''sun'''.” Not being much of a morning person, she winced internally. “First '''sun'''?” “It is the proper time, when the flowers of the pohoroh first open to the light.”}}\n# A revolution of the Earth around the Sun; a [[year]].\n# A transversing of the sky by the Sun; a [[day]].\n#* {{RQ:Haggard She|passage=Four '''suns''' since was the word brought to me from ‘''She-who-must-be-obeyed'',’ ‘White men come; if white men come, slay them not.’ Let them be brought to the house of ‘''She-who-must-be-obeyed''.’}}\n# The nineteenth [[trump]]/[[major arcana]] card of the [[tarot]].\n# {{lb|en|cartomancy}} The thirty-first [[Lenormand]] card.\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|sun god|sunbeat|sunblocker|sunlet|sunlighted|sunner|sunspecs\n|aftersun\n|antisun\n|catch the sun|Fifth Sun|sun goddess\n|countersun\n|day in the sun\n|everything under the sun\n|fix the roof while the sun is shining\n|fly too close to the sun\n|follow the sun\n|glory-of-the-sun\n|go to bed with the sun\n|have had one's day under the sun|sun animalcule|sun opal\n|have the sun in one's eyes\n|Land of the Ascendant Sun\n|low-sun\n|make hay while the sun shines\n|mean sun\n|midnight sun\n|mock sun\n|moment in the sun\n|nothing new under the sun\n|place in the sun|clear as the sun at noonday|sun orchid\n|protosun|sun god\n|purple glory-of-the-sun|sun helmet\n|rise with the sun\n|Rising Sun\n|stink like a mackerel in the sun\n|sun and planet gear\n|sun anemone shrimp\n|sunangel\n|sun-angel\n|sunback\n|sunbake|sun barge|sun deity\n|sun ball\n|sun bath|sun-bath|Sun-synchronous orbit\n|sunbath\n|sunbathe\n|sunbeam\n|sun bear\n|sunbeaten\n|sunbed\n|sun beetle\n|sunbelt\n|sunberry\n|sunbird\n|sun-bittern\n|sunbittern\n|sun bittern\n|sunbleached\n|sunbleak\n|sun blind\n|sunblind|sun-blind\n|sunblocking\n|sunblock|sun block\n|sunbloom\n|sunblotch\n|sunblush\n|sunbonneted|sun-bonneted\n|sunbonnet|sun bonnet\n|sunbow\n|sunbreak\n|sunbrella\n|sunbright\n|sunbrowned\n|sun bunny\n|sun-bunny\n|sunburn\n|sun-burner\n|sunburnt\n|sunburst\n|sun candle\n|suncap\n|suncapped\n|suncare\n|suncatcher\n|sunchair\n|sun-chaser\n|sunchoke\n|Sun City\n|Suncoast\n|suncolored\n|suncrack\n|suncream\n|sun cream\n|sun cross\n|suncup\n|sun cure\n|sundae\n|sundance|Sundance|sun dance\n|sun-darts\n|sundawn\n|Sunday\n|Sundayfied\n|sun deck\n|sundeck\n|sundew\n|sundial\n|sun disc\n|sundisk\n|sun dog\n|sundog\n|sundown\n|sun-drenched\n|sundress\n|sun-dried\n|sundrops\n|sun-dry\n|sunfall\n|sunfast\n|sun-fever\n|sun fever\n|sunfilled\n|sun filter\n|sunfish\n|sunfleck\n|sunflower\n|sunfringed\n|sunfrock\n|sunfruit\n|sungazer\n|sungazing\n|sun gear\n|sunglade\n|sunglass\n|sun-glassed\n|sunglasses\n|sun glasses\n|sunglint\n|sunglow\n|sungod\n|sun granny\n|sungrazer\n|sungrazing\n|sungrebe\n|sun hat\n|sunhat\n|sunhood\n|sun kicks\n|sun kink\n|sunkissed\n|sun-kissed\n|sun lamp\n|sunlamp\n|sunland\n|sunless\n|sun letter\n|sunlight\n|sunlighting\n|Sun-like\n|sunlike\n|sun-like\n|sun line\n|sunlit\n|sun lounge\n|sunlounger\n|sunly\n|sunnish\n|sunny\n|sun oneself\n|sun outage\n|sun painting\n|sun-parlor\n|sun parlor\n|sun parlour\n|sunperch\n|sunphotometer\n|sunphotometric\n|sunphotometry\n|sun picture\n|sun pillar\n|sun poisoning\n|sunporch\n|sunproof\n|sun protection factor\n|sunquake\n|sunquat\n|sunray\n|sunrise\n|sunrising\n|sunrist\n|sunroof\n|sun room\n|sunroom\n|sunroot\n|sunrose\n|sunscald\n|sunscreen\n|sunscreening\n|sunseed\n|sunseeker\n|sunset\n|sunshade\n|sunshaft\n|sunshield\n|sunshine\n|Sunshine\n|sun-shine\n|sun-shot\n|sun shot\n|sunshot\n|sunshower\n|sun shower\n|sun sign\n|sunskirter\n|sun sneezing\n|sunspace\n|sun spider\n|sun-splashed\n|sun spot\n|sunspot\n|sun spurge\n|sunstar\n|sun star\n|sunstead\n|sun-stead\n|sunstone\n|sunstricken\n|sunstrike\n|sunstroke\n|sunstruck\n|sunsuit\n|sunswept\n|sun-synchronous orbit\n|suntan\n|sun tea\n|suntiger\n|sun-tight\n|sun trap\n|suntrap\n|sun tunnel\n|sun umbrella\n|sun-up\n|sunup\n|sunview\n|sun visor\n|sunward\n|sunwards\n|sunwarmed\n|sunwashed\n|sunwatcher\n|sunways\n|sunwear\n|sunwing\n|sunwise\n|sun worshiper\n|sun-worshiper\n|sun worshipper\n|sun-worshipper\n|supersun\n|sure as the sun is going to come up tomorrow\n|sure as the sun is going to come up tomorrow morning\n|sure as the sun is going to rise tomorrow\n|sure as the sun is going to rise tomorrow morning\n|take the sun\n|there is nothing new under the sun\n|the sun is over the yardarm\n|the sun sets on something\n|think the sun shines out of someone's arse\n|think the sun shines out of someone's ass\n|think the sun shines out of someone's backside\n|think the sun shines out of someone's butt\n|time in the sun\n|too close to the sun\n|Tuscan sun\n|under the sun\n|Venezuelan suntiger\n|Vergina sun\n|virgin of the sun\n|what color is the sun in your world\n|where the sun doesn't shine\n|where the sun don't shine\n|Whitsun|Whitsunday\n|winter sun|sun oil|sun pipe|sun pan\n}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n{{col|en|south}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{see translation subpage|Noun}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{wikidata lexeme|L15739}}\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To expose to the heat and radiation of the sun.\n#: {{synonyms|en|apricate}}\n#: {{ux|en|Beautiful bodies lying on the beach, '''sunning''' their bronzed limbs.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2000|author=William Laurance|title=Stinging Trees and Wait-a-Whiles: Confessions of a Rainforest Biologist|passage=There were lots of zany antics and we tried not to stare too obviously at the beautiful women toplessly '''sunning''' themselves...}}\n#* {{RQ:Churchill Celebrity|chapter=2|passage='''Sunning''' himself on the board steps, I saw for the first time Mr. Farquhar Fenelon Cooke. He was dressed out in broad gaiters and bright tweeds, like an English tourist, and his face might have belonged to Dagon, idol of the Philistines. A silver snaffle on a heavy leather watch guard which connected the pockets of his corduroy waistcoat, together with a huge gold stirrup in his Ascot tie, sufficiently proclaimed his tastes.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To warm or dry in the sunshine.\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To be exposed to the sun.\n# {{lb|en|intransitive|alternative medicine}} To expose the [[eye]]s to the sun as part of the [[Bates method]].\n\n=====Hypernyms=====\n{{col|en|bask}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col|en|sun up}}\n\n=====Translations=====\n{{see translation subpage|Verb}}\n\n====See also====\n{{col4|en\n|aphelion\n|helio-\n|parhelion\n|perihelion\n|solar\n|sunn\n}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{der|en|ja|寸|tr=sun}}. {{doublet|en|cun}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|s|*}}\n\n# A [[traditional]] [[Japanese]] [[unit]] of [[length]], approximately 30.3 [[millimetre]]s (1.193 [[inch]]es).\n\n===Etymology 3===\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun|-}}\n\n# {{alt form|en|sunn||the plant}}.\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{pedia}}\n* {{R:OneLook}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=nsu|'uns|NUS|UNS|USN|uns}}\n\n{{cln|en|3-letter words}}\n{{C|en|Light sources}}\n\n==Bambara==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|bm|noun}}\n\n# [[trunk]] (of tree)\n\n=====Usage notes=====\nOften used in a compound with the name of a tree to indicate that kind of tree.\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{bor|bm|ar|صَوْم||fasting; abstaining from food, drink, and sex}}, from {{der|bm|syc|ܨܘܡܐ|tr=ṣawmāʾ}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|bm|noun}}\n\n# [[fasting]] (during the month of [[Ramadan]])\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|bm|verb}}\n\n# to [[fast]]\n\n==Bavarian==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|bar|sunn|suun}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|bar|gmh|sun}}, from {{inh|bar|goh|sunu}}, from {{inh|bar|gmw-pro|*sunu}}, from {{inh|bar|gem-pro|*sunuz||son}}. Cognate with {{cog|de|Sohn}}, {{cog|nl|zoon}}, {{cog|en|son}}, {{cog|is|sonur}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|bar|noun}}\n\n# {{lb|bar|Sauris}} [[son]]\n\n===References===\n* {{R:Patuzzi}}\n\n{{topics|bar|Family members|Male|People}}\n\n==Cimbrian==\n\n===Noun===\n{{cim-noun|m}}\n\n# {{lb|cim|Thirteen Communities}} [[son]]\n\n===References===\n* Umberto Patuzzi, ed., (2013) [https://web.archive.org/web/20201023025421/http://www.lusern.it/documenti/Centro_documentazione/libri-depliant-att--didattica-relazioni-etc-/libri/le-nostre-parole-luserna.pdf Ünsarne Börtar], Luserna: Comitato unitario delle linguistiche storiche germaniche in Italia / Einheitskomitee der historischen deutschen Sprachinseln in Italien\n\n{{C|cim|Family|Male|People}}\n\n==Czech==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{deverbal|cs|sunout}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{cs-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{cs-noun|m-in}}\n\n# [[slide]]\n\n====Declension====\n{{cs-ndecl|m}}\n\n====Related terms====\n{{col|cs|sunout|násun|odsun|podsun|posun|přesun|přísun|sesun|výsun|zásun}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:cs:PSJC}}\n* {{R:cs:SSJC}}\n* {{R:cs:IJP}}\n\n==Finnish==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{fi-pronunciation}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n{{etymid|fi|conjunction}}\nPossibly from {{m|fi|sun|id=pronoun form}} (etymology 2), originally as a replacement of {{m|fi||mun}}, eroded variant of {{m|fi|muin}} which was reinterpreted as the genitive singular of {{m|fi|mä}}.\n\n====Conjunction====\n{{fi-con}}\n\n# {{lb|fi|coordinating}} {{n-g|A coordinating conjunction expressing generality.}}\n#: {{ux|fi|En nyt jouda, kun tässä on sitä '''sun''' tätä tekemistä.\n|t=I don't have time for that because I have this '''and''' that to do (miscellaneous stuff/things to do).}}\n#: {{ux|fi|Lautanen oli täynnä makaroonilaatikkoa, makkaraa, salaattia, perunamuussia '''sun''' muuta pöperöä.\n|t=The plate was full of macaroni casserole, sausage, salad, mashed potatoes '''and''' other grub.}}\n\n====Further reading====\n* {{R:fi:KTSK|accessdate=2023-07-01}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymid|fi|pronoun form}}\nCompare standard {{m|fi|sinun||your, yours}} (genitive singular of {{m|fi|sinä}}).\n\n====Pronoun====\n{{head|fi|pronoun form}}\n\n# {{lb|fi|colloquial}} {{infl of|fi|sä||gen|s}}\n\n==Friulian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|fur|la|sonus}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{fur-noun|m}}\n\n# [[sound]]\n# [[music]]\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|music}} {{l|fur|musiche}}\n\n====Related terms====\n* {{l|fur|sunâ}}\n\n==Hokkien==\n{{zh-see|孫|poj}}\n\n==Inari Sami==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|smn|smi-pro|*sonë}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{rfp|smn}}\n\n===Pronoun===\n{{head|smn|pronoun|cat2=personal pronouns|genitive|suu}}\n\n# [[he]], [[she]], [[it]]\n\n===See also===\n{{smn-personal pronouns}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:smn:NDS-smnfin}}\n* {{R:Álgu|11357}}\n\n==Indonesian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|id|nl|zoen|t=kiss}}, from {{der|id|dum|zoene}}, {{m|dum|soen}}, {{m|dum|soene}}, {{m|dum|swoene||reconciliation; atonement; kiss}}, from {{der|id|odt|*sōna}}, {{m|odt|*swōna||reconciliation; peace; agreement}}, from {{der|id|gem-pro|*sōnō}}, {{m|gem-pro|*swōnō||appeasement; reconciliation; atonement; sacrifice}}, from {{der|id|ine-pro|*swā-n-||healthy; whole; active; vigorous}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|id|[ˈsʊn]}}\n* {{hyphenation|id|sun}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{id-noun}}\n\n# [[kiss]], a touch with the lips, usually to express love or affection, or as a greeting\n#: {{syn|id|ciuman}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|id\n|mengesun\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:KBBI Daring}}\n\n==Italian==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{m|it|su}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|it|/ˈsu.n‿/}}\n\n===Conjunction===\n{{head|it|preposition}}\n\n# {{tlb|it|poetic|rare}} {{alt form|it|su}} {{n-g|used before a [[vowel]]}}\n#* {{quote-book\n|it\n|start_year=mid 13<sup>th</sup> century\n|year=1280s\n|author=w:it:Ricordano Malispini\n|title=Istoria antica\n|title2=Istoria antica di Ricordano Malespini gentil'uomo fiorentino dall’edificazione di Fiorenza insino all'anno MCCLXXXI, con l'aggiunta di Giachetto suo nipote dal detto anno per insino al 1286\n|url=https://books.google.it/books?id=6NJSAAAAcAAJ&hl=it&pg=PA3#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|year2=1568\n|location2=Florence\n|publisher2=Stamperia Giunti\n|chapter=Come Catellino e sua gente sconfissano e amazorono Fiorino; e della venuta di Giulio Cesare con l’oste de’ romani\n|trans-chapter=How Catiline and his people defeated and killed Fiorinus; and of the arrival of Julius Caesar with the Roman host\n|chapter_number=16\n|page2=9\n|pageurl2=https://books.google.it/books?id=6NJSAAAAcAAJ&hl=it&pg=PA11-IA16#v=onepage&q&f=false\n|text={{...}} preſſo a monte Giulio Ceſare ſi puoſe la milizia di Magrino {{...}}, & in '''ſun'''’unaltro monte preſſo a quello {{...}}\n|norm={{...}} presso a Monte Giulio Cesare si puose la milizia di Magrino {{...}}; e in '''sun''' un altro monte, presso a quello {{...}}\n|t={{...}} Macrinus' force was stationed near Mount Julius Caesar {{...}}; and, '''on''' another mountain, near that one {{...}}\n}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:it:Trec}}\n\n==Japanese==\n\n===Romanization===\n{{ja-romaji}}\n\n# {{ja-romanization of|すん}}\n\n==Javanese==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|jv|noun}}\n\n# a [[kiss]]\n\n==Kaingang==\n{{was fwotd|kgp|2013|May|12}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|kgp|/ˈʃudn/}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|kgp|verb}}\n\n# To [[warm]] oneself by staying near a [[fire]].<ref>{{R:Dicionário Kaingang-Português|page=83}}</ref>\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n==Kamkata-viri==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from a descendant of {{der|bsh|sa|सुवर्ण|tr=suvárṇa}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|bsh|noun|g=m}} {{q|Western, Northeastern, Southeastern}}<ref name=\"NEL\">{{R:iir-nur:NEL|s′un}}</ref><ref>Halfmann, Jakob (2024). A Grammatical Description of the Katë Language (Nuristani) (PhD thesis). Köln: Universität zu Köln.</ref>\n\n# [[gold]]\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n==Ladin==\n\n===Preposition===\n{{head|lld|preposition}}\n\n# [[on]], [[over]]\n# [[in]]\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|lld|verb form}}\n\n# {{alternative form of|lld|son}}\n\n==Manchu==\n\n===Romanization===\n{{head|mnc|romanization|sc=Latn}}\n\n# {{romanization of|mnc|ᠰᡠᠨ}}\n\n==Mandarin==\n\n===Romanization===\n{{cmn-pinyin|notr=1}}\n\n# {{nonstandard spelling of|cmn|sc=Latn|sūn}}\n# {{nonstandard spelling of|cmn|sc=Latn|sǔn}}\n# {{nonstandard spelling of|cmn|sc=Latn|sùn}}\n\n====Usage notes====\n* {{cmn-toneless-note}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|enm|noun}}\n\n# {{alt form|enm|sonne|t=sun|id=sun}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|enm|noun}}\n\n# {{alt form|enm|sone|id=son|t=son}}\n\n==Middle High German==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|gmh|suon|sūn|son}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{inh+|gmh|goh|sunu}}, from {{inh|gmh|gmw-pro|*sunu}}, from {{inh|gmh|gem-pro|*sunuz}}, from {{inh|gmh|ine-pro|*suHnús}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{gmh-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|gmh|noun|g=m}}\n\n# {{l|en|son}}\n\n====Declension====\n{{gmh-ndecl|m.genes:s.nompl:süne.genpl:süne.datpl:sünen}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|gsw|-}}\n*: Italian Walser: {{l|gsw|su}}, {{l|gsw|ŝchu}}\n* {{desc|bar|-}}\n*: {{desc|cim|zun|alts=1}}\n*: {{desc|mhn|su'}}\n*: Udinese: {{l|bar|sun}}, {{l|bar|sunn}}, {{l|bar|suun}}\n* {{desc|gmw-cfr|-}}\n*: {{desc|hrx|Sohn}}\n* {{desc|de|Sohn}}\n* {{desc|gmw-rfr|-}}\n*: {{desc|pdc|Soh}}\n* {{desc|wym|zun|zūn}}\n* {{desc|yi|זון}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:gmh:BMZ|entry=sun|id=S07229}}\n* {{R:gmh:Köbler}}\n\n{{c|gmh|Male family members}}\n\n==Mimi of Nachtigal==\n\n===Etymology===\nSimilar to (and likely a borrowing of, or possibly the lender of) the word used for water in the \"third Mimi\" language, {{cog|amj|sunu}}, which in turn is (per Starostin) \"most likely cognate with\" {{cog|fvr|suːn||waterhole, well}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|mis-mmn|noun}}\n\n# [[water]]\n\n===References===\n* George Starostin, ''On Mimi''\n\n==North Frisian==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alt|frr|sönj||Mooring}}\n* {{alt|frr|Sön||Sylt}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|frr|ofs|sand}}, from {{inh|frr|gem-pro|*samdaz}}. Cognates include {{cog|fy|sân}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|frr|noun|g=n}}\n\n# {{lb|frr|Föhr-Amrum}} [[sand]]\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|frr|noun|g=m|plural|sunen}}\n\n# {{lb|frr|Föhr-Amrum}} [[sandbank]], sandy area, [[sands]]\n\n===Derived terms===\n{{col4|frr\n|sunbonk\n|sunbeenk\n|sunglees\n|sunig\n|sunkast\n|sunkurn\n|sunkuuk\n|sunküül\n|sunpapiar\n|sunrag\n|sunseek\n|sunskol\n|sunstoof\n|sunstrun\n|suntoort\n|sunwaal\n|sunwai\n}}\n\n==Old Danish==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|gmq-oda|non|sonr}}, {{m|non|sunr}}, from {{inh|gmq-oda|gem-pro|*sunuz}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|gmq-oda|noun|g=m|nominative plural|synær}}\n\n# [[son]]\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|da|søn}}\n\n==Old French==\n\n===Determiner===\n{{head|fro|determiner}}\n\n# {{lb|fro|Anglo-Norman}} {{alternative form of|fro|son}}\n\n==Quiripi==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|qyp|noun}}\n\n# {{lb|qyp|Unquachog}} [[stone]]\n\n===References===\n* {{cite-text|qyp|year=1791|author={{w|Thomas Jefferson}}|title=A vocabulary of the Language of the Unquachog Indians}}\n\n==Romanian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|ro|/ˈsun/}}\n* {{rhymes|ro|un|s=1}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|ro|verb form}}\n\n# {{verb form of|ro|suna||1|s|pres|ind//sub}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nProbably from {{inh|ro|la|sonus}}, or from the verb {{m|ro|suna}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{ro-noun|n|sunuri}}\n\n# {{lb|ro|obsolete}} [[sound]]\n#: {{syn|ro|sunet}}\n\n=====Declension=====\n{{ro-noun-n-uri}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:DEX}}\n\n==Scots==\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|sco|ang|sunne}}, from {{inh|sco|gmw-pro|*sunnā}}, from {{inh|sco|gem-pro|*sunnǭ}}, from [[heteroclitic]] [[inanimate]] {{inh|sco|ine-pro||*sh₂wen-|t=sun}}, oblique stem {{m|ine-pro|*sóh₂wl̥|t=sun}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|sco|/sʌn/|/sɪn/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sco-noun}}\n\n# [[sun#English|sun]]\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col4|sco\n|sunblink\n|sundoun\n|sunlicht\n|sunsheen\n}}\n\n==Vietnamese==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{vi-IPA}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{vi-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|vi|intransitive}} To [[shrink]].\n# {{lb|vi|transitive}} To [[pull together]].\n#: '''''sun''' vai''\n#:: to pull one’s shoulders together\n\n===References===\n* {{R:FVDP}}\n\n==Waigali==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from a descendant of {{der|wbk|sa|सुवर्ण|tr=suvárṇa}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|wbk|/ˈsun/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|wbk|noun}} {{q|Nisheigram}}<ref name=\"NEL\">{{R:iir-nur:NEL|sun}}</ref>\n\n# [[gold]]\n\n===References===\n<references />\n\n==Yoruba==\n\n===Etymology 1===\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{yo-IPA|sùn}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{yo-verb|sùn}}\n\n# to [[sleep]]\n#: {{uxi|yo|Mo '''sùn''' [[gbalaja]]|I '''slept''' stretched out}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n{{dialect synonyms|yo|sùn}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col3|yo\n|àsùngbádùn <t:good night's sleep>\n|ibùsùn <t:bed>\n|sísùn <t:sleeping>\n|kòríkòsùn <t:close friend>\n|àìróorunsùn <t:insomnia>\n|másùnmáwo <t:stress>\n|àsùnwọra <t:deep sleep>\n}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{etymid|yo|to roast, burn}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{yo-IPA|sun}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{yo-verb|sun}}\n\n# {{senseid|yo|to roast}} to [[roast]]\n#: {{syn|yo|yan|{{l|yo|wì|t=to singe}}}}\n#: {{uxi|yo|Mo '''sun''' ẹran.|I '''roasted''' the meat.}}\n# {{senseid|yo|to burn}} to [[burn]]; to [[set on fire]]\n#: {{syn|yo|jó|jóná|dáná sun}}\n#: {{uxi|yo|A máa ń '''sun''' òkú nínú àṣà tèmi.|We '''cremate''' the dead in my culture.}}\n#: {{uxi|yo|Àwọn jagunjagun ya wọ̀lú, wọ́n sì '''dáná sun''' ojúbọ|The warriors raided the town and '''set''' the shrines '''on fire'''}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n{{dialect synonyms|yo|sun|id=to roast, burn}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col2|yo\n|ìdánásunlé <t:arson>\n|ìdánásungbó <t:arson; slash and burn>\n|sísun <t:burning>\n|dáná sun\n}}\n\n===Etymology 3===\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{yo-IPA|sun}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{yo-verb|sun}}\n\n# to [[trickle]]; to [[flow]]\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|yo|orísun|t=source}}\n\n===Etymology 4===\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{yo-IPA|sun}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{yo-verb|sun}}\n\n# {{senseid|yo|to cry}} {{lb|yo|with {{l|yo|ẹkún|t=tears}}}} to [[cry]]\n#: {{uxi|yo|Wọ́n ń '''sun''' ẹkún níbi ìsìnkú|They're crying at the burial ground}}\n# to [[chant]]\n#: {{uxi|yo|Ọdẹ ni ó máa ń '''sun''' ìjálá, ìyàwó ni ó máa ń '''sun''' ẹkún-ìyàwó|Hunters chant {{l|yo|ìjálá}}, and brides '''chant''' the {{l|yo|ẹkún-ìyàwó}}}}\n\n=====Synonyms=====\n{{dialect synonyms|yo|sun|id=to cry}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n{{col2|yo\n|sunkún <t:to cry>\n|sísun <t:chanting; crying>\n}}\n\n===Etymology 5===\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{yo-IPA|sùn}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{yo-verb|sùn}}\n\n# to [[aim]]; to [[target]]\n#: {{uxi|yo|Ìyẹn ni mò ń '''fojú sùn''' lọ́dún tó ń bọ̀|That's what I '''aspire for''' this coming year}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|yo|àfojúsùn|t=goal; target}}\n\n===Etymology 6===\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{yo-IPA|sún}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{yo-verb|sún}}\n\n# to [[shift]]; to [[move]]\n#: {{uxi|yo|'''Sún''' mọ́ mi.|'''Move''' closer to me.}}\n#: {{uxi|yo|Pẹ̀lúmi fẹ́ '''sún''' ìpàdé '''[[síwájú]]'''|Pelumi wants to '''postpone''' the meeting}}\n# to [[nudge]]; to [[motivate]]\n#: {{uxi|yo|Ó '''sún''' mi láti wọ́de|It '''motivated''' me to protest}}\n# to [[prick]]\n#: {{syn|yo|gún}}\n#: {{uxi|yo|Ẹ̀gún '''sún''' mi lọ́wọ́|The thorn '''pricked''' me}}\n\n=====Derived terms=====\n* {{l|yo|sún kì|t=to contract; to shrink}}\n\n===Etymology 7===\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{yo-IPA|sùn}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{yo-verb|sùn}}\n\n# to make a [[complaint]]\n#: {{uxi|yo|A ti '''fẹjọ́''' yín '''sùn''' wọ́n|We have '''reported''' you to them}}"}}